"```sql\nSELECT \n  (COUNT(DISTINCT c.id) * 100.0 / COUNT(DISTINCT c_all.id)) AS percentage\nFROM \n  cards c\nJOIN \n  set_translations st ON c.setCode = st.setCode\nJOIN \n  sets s ON c.setCode = s.code\nWHERE \n  st.language = 'Chinese Simplified' \n  AND c.isOnlineOnly = 1\n  AND s.isOnlineOnly = 1\n```\nThis SQL query calculates the percentage of cards that are only available for online games and have Chinese Simplified as the language. It joins the `cards`, `set_translations`, and `sets` tables to filter the cards based on the specified conditions. The percentage is calculated by dividing the count of such cards by the total count of cards, then multiplying by 100."